//Introduction Section
.container
    .col-md-9.col-lg-9.col-sm-9
        .project-title RECOVERY: Earthquake Edition
        .row.section-header Overview
        .row
            p I worked in a team of four undergraduate students to create a card game prototype to teach college students about earthquake recovery. The idea was proposed to my team by our sponsor, Scott Miles from The Center for Collaborative Systems for Security, Safety, and Regional Resilience (CoSSaR).
        .row.section-header Problem Statement
        .row
            p Earthquake recovery is a probable threat in the Pacific Northwest. 
            .col-lg-6.col-md-6.col-sm-12.col-xs-12.section-tile
                | Based on web research:
                ul
                    li recovery is long-term, sometimes lasting 10+ years
                    li recovery heavily involves collaboration and cooperation between emergency managers
                    li recovery does not always mean building back to the normal state
            .col-lg-6.col-md-6.col-sm-12.col-xs-12.section-tile
                | Based on user surveys:
                ul
                    li there is a lack of user knowledge on disaster recovery
                    li participants defined recovery as short-term and focused on survival
                    li participants did not mention improvements in definition    
        .row.section-header Design Questions
            .design-question-statement
                span “
                | What does recovery look like after a disaster? What are real world examples of approaches and challenges to disaster recovery?
                span ”
            .design-question-statement
                span “
                | What types of existing board game mechanisms are there? 
                span ”   
        .row.section-header Solution
            p RECOVERY: Earthquake Edition is an educational card game adapted from the existing card game called TOURING from Winning Moves Inc. RECOVERY edu- cates its players on earthquake recovery. In this 3-4 player game, each player takes on the role of an emergency manager of their own city, all of which have been struck by an earthquake. The goal of the game is to rebuild your city in- cluding houses, businesses, fire stations, and schools.                     
    .col-md-3.col-lg-3.com-sm-3
        h3 Duration
        p 20 weeks
        h3 Team
        ul.list-not-decorated 
            li Shelley Eang
            li Michael Chen
            li Khalil Somani
            li Amy Tang
        h3 My Role
        ul.list-not-decorated 
            li UX/UI
            li Visual Designer
            li User Researcher
        h3 Skills
        ul.list-not-decorated 
            li Illustrator
            li Figma             
